===Etymology===
Latin ''[[abominatus]]'', past participle of ''[[abominari]]'' to [[deprecate]] as [[ominous]], to [[abhor]], to curse; ''[[ab]]'' + ''omen'' a [[foreboding]]. See [[omen]]
===Transitive verb===
Imperfect and past participle: '''Abominated'''<br>
Present participle: '''Abominating'''
#To turn from as [[ill-omened]]; to hate in the highest degree, as if with religious dread; [[loathe]]; as, to ''abominate'' all [[impiety]].
===Synonyms===
*To [[hate]]; [[abhor]]; loathe; [[detest]]
